react project -

- create a folder 
-open in vs-code 
-open terminal 
-install - the below command 
		 - npm create vite@latest - y - .(dot) for current folder structure - react (as framework) - java script (select varient) - no- no-
		 - to install node module - npm i 
		 - npm run dev - to run and start the server 
		 
- install react router -
		- npm i react-router-dom
		
- go to vs code - click on Extension left side menu - search - ES7+ React/Redux/React-Native snippets
		- install it - 
		
- go to App.jsx - remove all and type  rafc and select the 1st one.
	 export default App
- add - tailwindcss in to project 
	- search in google - tailwindcss and open the 1st link 
	- open goto - Docs - click on "using Vite" 
	- copy the command which are under "terminal". - npm install tailwindcss @tailwindcss/vite
	- in the website - vite.config.ts - copy the "import tailwindcss from '@tailwindcss/vite'" and past inside ur project "vite.config.js"
	- in the web page - copy "plugins" like - tailwindcss(), and past it inside the "vite.config.ts"  after [react(),(past here ----)]
	- goto main index.css and past "@import "tailwindcss";"
this is how tailwindcss will install in your project 

- go to index.css - remove all and type 
	body{
	background-color: black;
	}

- install React-toastify
npm i react-toastify

